1
00:00:02,250 --> 00:00:05,333
- Step right up!
- I've got fresh fruit here!

2
00:00:05,416 --> 00:00:07,291
<i>[tense music]</i>

3
00:00:07,375 --> 00:00:09,750
- [stammering]

4
00:00:11,125 --> 00:00:12,958
- I'll ask one more time.

5
00:00:13,041 --> 00:00:15,750
Why did you call me by
the name of the Witch of Envy?

6
00:00:15,833 --> 00:00:17,000
[stammers]

7
00:00:17,083 --> 00:00:18,041
W--well, because you said
I should.

8
00:00:18,125 --> 00:00:19,583
- I don't know who told you that

9
00:00:19,666 --> 00:00:21,541
but they have
a terrible sense of humor.

10
00:00:21,625 --> 00:00:24,125
The Witch of Envy is the very
definition of taboo,

11
00:00:24,208 --> 00:00:26,083
and you call me by her name

12
00:00:26,166 --> 00:00:27,250
which most dare
not even say yes?

13
00:00:27,333 --> 00:00:28,375
- Yeah, she's right, kid.

14
00:00:28,458 --> 00:00:30,125
- You crossed the line
there, buddy.

15
00:00:30,875 --> 00:00:32,416
- If you don't
have anything to say,

16
00:00:32,500 --> 00:00:34,375
then I'm leaving.
I have things to do.

17
00:00:34,458 --> 00:00:36,208
- What?

18
00:00:36,291 --> 00:00:38,041
- [giggles]

19
00:00:38,125 --> 00:00:39,208
- [stammers]

20
00:00:39,291 --> 00:00:40,750
That's Felt.
[grunts]

21
00:00:44,708 --> 00:00:46,041
- [gasps]

22
00:00:47,958 --> 00:00:49,541
[gasping]

23
00:00:51,083 --> 00:00:52,416
[gasps]

24
00:00:52,500 --> 00:00:54,750
Wait, were you a distraction?
Are you working with her?

25
00:00:54,833 --> 00:00:55,875
- [grunts]

26
00:00:55,958 --> 00:00:56,916
What?
No!

27
00:00:57,000 --> 00:00:58,750
- [grunting]

28
00:00:58,833 --> 00:01:00,083
- Hey, wait a minute.
Come back here.

29
00:01:00,166 --> 00:01:02,041
You've got it all wrong.

30
00:01:02,125 --> 00:01:03,333
[grunts]

31
00:01:04,666 --> 00:01:05,791
[gasps]

32
00:01:05,875 --> 00:01:07,041
Damn it.

33
00:01:08,375 --> 00:01:11,291
<i>[Konomi Suzuki's "Redo"]</i>

34
00:01:11,375 --> 00:01:18,291
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35
00:01:18,375 --> 00:01:21,291
<i>- [singing in Japanese]</i>

36
00:01:21,375 --> 00:01:28,458
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37
00:01:47,500 --> 00:01:54,500
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38
00:02:15,750 --> 00:02:22,791
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39
00:02:38,416 --> 00:02:43,708
- [panting]

40
00:02:43,791 --> 00:02:45,000
Come on.

41
00:02:45,083 --> 00:02:47,375
Would someone please
be a little nicer to me?

42
00:02:47,458 --> 00:02:49,000
[breathing heavily]

43
00:02:49,083 --> 00:02:50,916
This world sucks.

44
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:52,791
[breathing heavily]

45
00:02:52,875 --> 00:02:54,916
Why was I even summoned here?

46
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:56,291
[gasping]

47
00:02:56,375 --> 00:02:58,208
- What are you going on
and on about?

48
00:02:58,291 --> 00:02:59,375
- If you don't want
to get hurt

49
00:02:59,458 --> 00:03:00,875
then cough up
whatever you've got.

50
00:03:00,958 --> 00:03:02,500
[both chuckling]

51
00:03:03,875 --> 00:03:05,791
Just stop it already!
all: Huh?

52
00:03:05,875 --> 00:03:08,541
Nobody could be
this damn persistent.

53
00:03:08,625 --> 00:03:10,500
- You think you can mouth off
to us?

54
00:03:10,583 --> 00:03:11,500
- Now move it!

55
00:03:11,583 --> 00:03:12,708
I have somewhere I need to go

56
00:03:12,791 --> 00:03:14,333
and you guys are in my way.

57
00:03:14,416 --> 00:03:16,125
[gasps]

58
00:03:19,083 --> 00:03:21,500
- [grunting]

59
00:03:21,583 --> 00:03:24,375
You stabbed him?

60
00:03:24,458 --> 00:03:25,708
Oh, man.
Now you've done it.

61
00:03:25,791 --> 00:03:27,750
<i>- You've gotta be kidding.</i>
<i>It hurts.</i>

62
00:03:27,833 --> 00:03:29,916
<i>It hurts.</i>

63
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:32,291
[coughs]

64
00:03:32,375 --> 00:03:34,000
- Hey, what are you doing?

65
00:03:34,083 --> 00:03:35,625
- Well, no sense in wasting him!

66
00:03:35,708 --> 00:03:36,958
Take anything he's got
that's worth selling!

67
00:03:37,041 --> 00:03:38,041
- Huh?

68
00:03:38,125 --> 00:03:40,583
[both shouting]

69
00:03:40,666 --> 00:03:42,416
<i>[tense music]</i>

70
00:03:42,500 --> 00:03:45,125
<i>- But Old Man Rom ate those.</i>

71
00:03:45,208 --> 00:03:50,125
<i>How c--could this be?</i>

72
00:03:50,208 --> 00:03:52,333
- Come on, move it!
Run!

73
00:03:52,416 --> 00:03:55,333
[both breathing heavily]

74
00:03:55,416 --> 00:03:59,333
<i>♪ ♪</i>

75
00:04:03,041 --> 00:04:05,125
- Speak up.
You want it?

76
00:04:07,666 --> 00:04:10,375
- Hey, mister?
- Huh?

77
00:04:10,458 --> 00:04:12,833
- How many times have you
seen me here before?

78
00:04:12,916 --> 00:04:15,666
- What are you talking about?
I've never seen you before.

79
00:04:15,750 --> 00:04:17,833
Well, decide.
You want it?

80
00:04:17,916 --> 00:04:19,166
- [chuckles]

81
00:04:20,791 --> 00:04:23,000
Sorry, but I don't
have any money at all.

82
00:04:23,083 --> 00:04:24,666
Totally broke.

83
00:04:24,750 --> 00:04:27,041
- The get the hell out of here!

84
00:04:27,125 --> 00:04:30,333
- Wallet, cell phone,
corn potage, cup of noodles.

85
00:04:30,416 --> 00:04:33,666
It looks like my track suit
and sneakers are intact, too,

86
00:04:33,750 --> 00:04:35,375
and hopefully...

87
00:04:37,208 --> 00:04:38,833
Oh, that's a relief,

88
00:04:38,916 --> 00:04:40,000
'cause a wound to the back

89
00:04:40,083 --> 00:04:42,833
is a warriors greatest shame
for sure.

90
00:04:42,916 --> 00:04:44,291
[grunts]

91
00:04:44,375 --> 00:04:46,875
Well, with this much
circumstantial evidence,

92
00:04:46,958 --> 00:04:48,708
there's absolutely
no denying it.

93
00:04:49,250 --> 00:04:53,541
It's kind of hard to believe
but this has to be

94
00:04:53,625 --> 00:04:55,666
a time leap,
and each time,

95
00:04:55,750 --> 00:05:00,791
I returned to my initial State.
I'll call it Return by Death.

96
00:05:01,625 --> 00:05:03,625
[animal grunts]

97
00:05:05,666 --> 00:05:08,208
So I have the ability
to leap backwards in time,

98
00:05:08,291 --> 00:05:09,708
but it only
activates when I die.

99
00:05:09,791 --> 00:05:12,666
Guess even my special power
knows what a loser I am.

100
00:05:13,500 --> 00:05:15,916
If I've gone back in time
to this moment once again,

101
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:17,500
then Satella hasn't helped me.

102
00:05:17,583 --> 00:05:19,625
We haven't even met yet.

103
00:05:19,958 --> 00:05:21,625
Consequently,
that means the debt I owed her

104
00:05:21,708 --> 00:05:23,958
for saving me
is completely gone.

105
00:05:24,375 --> 00:05:26,416
That's actually a stroke
of good luck.

106
00:05:26,500 --> 00:05:28,208
I can forget everything,
sell this,

107
00:05:28,291 --> 00:05:29,625
save some funds,

108
00:05:29,708 --> 00:05:31,041
and use my knowledge
of the modern world

109
00:05:31,125 --> 00:05:34,416
to create a paradise.
Things are finally looking up.

110
00:05:34,500 --> 00:05:36,458
- Huh?
- Am I right, mister?

111
00:05:36,541 --> 00:05:38,708
- W--why are you asking me?

112
00:05:38,791 --> 00:05:41,458
I don't have any idea what
you're talking about, all right?

113
00:05:41,541 --> 00:05:43,750
- Come on.
Don't be like that.

114
00:05:43,833 --> 00:05:46,875
- I don't want to get caught up
in other people's problems,

115
00:05:46,958 --> 00:05:48,291
so don't talk to me about 'em.

116
00:05:48,375 --> 00:05:49,916
- [grunts]

117
00:05:50,000 --> 00:05:52,958
<i>Well, I guess the old saying</i>
<i>"let sleeping dogs lie"</i>

118
00:05:53,041 --> 00:05:55,583
<i>applies no matter</i>
<i>what world you're on.</i>

119
00:05:56,333 --> 00:05:59,583
<i>Even so,</i>
<i>there are always softies---</i>

120
00:05:59,666 --> 00:06:00,916
<i>people who will help others,</i>

121
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:03,416
<i>even when they really</i>
<i>can't afford to.</i>

122
00:06:03,500 --> 00:06:05,416
<i>She just had</i>
<i>something precious stolen.</i>

123
00:06:05,500 --> 00:06:07,750
<i>She didn't have time for me.</i>

124
00:06:07,833 --> 00:06:10,250
<i>Yet she saved</i>
<i>some useless stranger</i>

125
00:06:10,333 --> 00:06:12,083
<i>and even healed him.</i>

126
00:06:12,166 --> 00:06:14,125
<i>Then she let that</i>
<i>useless stranger</i>

127
00:06:14,208 --> 00:06:16,125
<i>feel pleased with himself.</i>

128
00:06:16,208 --> 00:06:17,458
[grunts]

129
00:06:17,541 --> 00:06:19,791
<i>[tense music]</i>

130
00:06:19,875 --> 00:06:21,458
[grunts]

131
00:06:21,541 --> 00:06:24,666
<i>♪ ♪</i>

132
00:06:24,750 --> 00:06:26,125
[gasps]

133
00:06:26,208 --> 00:06:28,166
<i>♪ ♪</i>

134
00:06:28,250 --> 00:06:29,791
[gasps]

135
00:06:29,875 --> 00:06:32,791
<i>♪ ♪</i>

136
00:06:32,875 --> 00:06:34,291
[gasps]

137
00:06:34,375 --> 00:06:41,291
<i>♪ ♪</i>

138
00:06:41,375 --> 00:06:42,958
<i>Even if Satella</i>
<i>doesn't know me,</i>

139
00:06:43,041 --> 00:06:45,166
<i>that doesn't change everything.</i>

140
00:06:45,250 --> 00:06:48,833
<i>Felt still stole her insignia</i>
<i>and Elsa will--</i>

141
00:06:50,166 --> 00:06:51,833
<i>No matter how</i>
<i>many times I repeat this,</i>

142
00:06:51,916 --> 00:06:53,250
<i>that won't change.</i>

143
00:06:53,333 --> 00:06:55,125
<i>History's a compelling force,</i>
<i>right?</i>

144
00:06:55,208 --> 00:07:00,166
<i>♪ ♪</i>

145
00:07:00,250 --> 00:07:01,625
[grunts]

146
00:07:02,250 --> 00:07:05,375
<i>Yeah, if I'm fully aware</i>
<i>that people I used to know</i>

147
00:07:05,458 --> 00:07:06,791
<i>will be murdered...</i>

148
00:07:08,791 --> 00:07:11,250
Then I can't just ignore it.

149
00:07:12,791 --> 00:07:15,000
[panting]

150
00:07:15,083 --> 00:07:16,375
- Huh?

151
00:07:16,458 --> 00:07:18,125
- Hey, mister.

152
00:07:18,208 --> 00:07:20,000
- What do you want now,
broke boy?

153
00:07:20,083 --> 00:07:22,916
- There's something
I need to ask you.

154
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:24,000
Have there been any

155
00:07:24,083 --> 00:07:25,875
pick pocketing incidents
around here?

156
00:07:25,958 --> 00:07:27,833
- Asking questions
without buying, huh?

157
00:07:27,916 --> 00:07:29,875
You got some nerve, kid.
- [grunts]

158
00:07:29,958 --> 00:07:32,166
- But yeah, stuff like
that happens all the time.

159
00:07:32,250 --> 00:07:33,458
- [grunts]

160
00:07:33,541 --> 00:07:35,208
- Though that last one
was unusual.

161
00:07:35,291 --> 00:07:36,125
- [gasps]

162
00:07:36,208 --> 00:07:37,500
- They threw some magic around

163
00:07:37,583 --> 00:07:39,125
in the street a couple of times.

164
00:07:39,208 --> 00:07:41,041
Things that look like icicles
flew around

165
00:07:41,125 --> 00:07:42,500
and lodged in the wall.

166
00:07:42,583 --> 00:07:44,958
They disappeared quick though.
- I was too late.

167
00:07:45,041 --> 00:07:47,500
I thought if I could keep
the insignia from being stolen

168
00:07:47,583 --> 00:07:48,875
then maybe things wouldn't
have--

169
00:07:48,958 --> 00:07:50,583
- What are you going on about?

170
00:07:50,666 --> 00:07:52,625
- Oh, it's nothing important,
but, uh...

171
00:07:53,791 --> 00:07:55,375
Thanks, mister.
Really.

172
00:07:55,458 --> 00:07:57,875
You helped me even though
I didn't actually buy anything.

173
00:07:57,958 --> 00:07:59,666
- Ah, it's no big deal.

174
00:07:59,958 --> 00:08:02,458
A broke kid a lot like yourself
just helped my daughter

175
00:08:02,541 --> 00:08:04,541
after she got separated
from her mother earlier.

176
00:08:04,625 --> 00:08:06,208
- [gasps]

177
00:08:06,291 --> 00:08:08,875
I guess fate
is a compelling force, too.

178
00:08:08,958 --> 00:08:10,375
Huh.
[chuckles]

179
00:08:10,458 --> 00:08:13,291
- What are you smiling about?
- It's nothing.

180
00:08:13,958 --> 00:08:15,875
I'll be sure to buy
an appa next time, okay?

181
00:08:15,958 --> 00:08:16,916
- Sounds good.

182
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:18,375
Buy one
and you'll be a customer.

183
00:08:18,458 --> 00:08:19,875
Get to work, broke boy!

184
00:08:19,958 --> 00:08:22,208
See you!
- Later!

185
00:08:22,750 --> 00:08:24,375
This means there's only one way.

186
00:08:24,833 --> 00:08:27,083
I have to by the insignia
from felt before Elsa comes

187
00:08:27,166 --> 00:08:28,750
to the loot house
and return it to Satella.

188
00:08:28,833 --> 00:08:30,083
Wait.

189
00:08:30,166 --> 00:08:32,500
Satella was just an alias
that she used, wasn't it?

190
00:08:33,916 --> 00:08:36,208
Then I'm gonna need to do
whatever I can this time around

191
00:08:36,291 --> 00:08:38,416
to make sure she tells me
what her real name actually is.

192
00:08:38,500 --> 00:08:39,583
[grunts]

193
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:43,250
- What are you going on
and on about?

194
00:08:43,333 --> 00:08:44,416
- If you don't want
to get hurt,

195
00:08:44,500 --> 00:08:46,416
then cough up
whatever you've got.

196
00:08:46,500 --> 00:08:48,083
- Listen Dumb, Dumber,
and Dumberest.

197
00:08:48,166 --> 00:08:50,125
I'm getting sick
of seeing your faces.

198
00:08:50,208 --> 00:08:52,250
After doing this four times,
I've learned my lesson.

199
00:08:52,333 --> 00:08:53,583
all: Huh?

200
00:08:53,666 --> 00:08:55,708
- [inhales]

201
00:08:59,833 --> 00:09:01,750
Guards, help me!

202
00:09:01,833 --> 00:09:03,791
- What the hell, you bastard?

203
00:09:03,875 --> 00:09:04,791
- [chuckles]

204
00:09:04,875 --> 00:09:05,791
<i>It seems my memory</i>

205
00:09:05,875 --> 00:09:07,250
<i>from before was right.</i>

206
00:09:07,333 --> 00:09:10,125
<i>This world does have</i>
<i>some kind of police force.</i>

207
00:09:10,208 --> 00:09:12,750
Someone!
[gasping]

208
00:09:12,833 --> 00:09:14,625
Please, I need a man!

209
00:09:14,708 --> 00:09:15,625
- Damn it.
Shut up!

210
00:09:15,708 --> 00:09:17,541
- No, don't touch me!
Stop!

211
00:09:17,625 --> 00:09:19,958
I can't hear you!
You're not being sincere enough!

212
00:09:20,041 --> 00:09:23,458
Someone please help me!
Please!

213
00:09:23,541 --> 00:09:24,500
Huh?

214
00:09:24,583 --> 00:09:26,583
- Don't scare me like that.

215
00:09:26,666 --> 00:09:28,791
All that yelling
freaked me out a little bit.

216
00:09:28,875 --> 00:09:30,291
- Just a little bit, though.

217
00:09:30,375 --> 00:09:32,291
- Yeah, just a teeny
tiny little bit.

218
00:09:32,375 --> 00:09:34,125
- [stammers]

219
00:09:34,208 --> 00:09:36,375
- Trying to run away
won't help you.

220
00:09:36,458 --> 00:09:38,416
- [winces]

221
00:09:38,500 --> 00:09:39,375
- That's enough.

222
00:09:39,458 --> 00:09:41,000
[all grunting]

223
00:09:44,166 --> 00:09:47,500
- Red hair and a knight's sword
with scratches made

224
00:09:47,583 --> 00:09:49,000
by dragon cloth.

225
00:09:49,083 --> 00:09:52,500
Can that be Reinhard?

226
00:09:52,583 --> 00:09:54,666
The master swordsman?

227
00:09:55,208 --> 00:09:57,791
- Looks like I don't need
to introduce myself.

228
00:09:58,583 --> 00:09:59,833
Thought to be honest,

229
00:09:59,916 --> 00:10:01,333
that nickname
is a bit much for me.

230
00:10:01,416 --> 00:10:02,416
I don't know how much help

231
00:10:02,500 --> 00:10:04,125
my modest strength
can be to him,

232
00:10:04,208 --> 00:10:06,541
but if you wish to resort
to extreme measures,

233
00:10:06,625 --> 00:10:07,875
let me warn you.

234
00:10:07,958 --> 00:10:10,958
As a knight,
I will have to fight back.

235
00:10:11,041 --> 00:10:13,208
- S--screw this business.

236
00:10:13,291 --> 00:10:14,333
It's not worth it!

237
00:10:14,416 --> 00:10:19,083
[all shouting]

238
00:10:19,166 --> 00:10:21,166
Glad we both came out
of that unscathed.

239
00:10:21,250 --> 00:10:22,583
Lucky break, huh?

240
00:10:22,666 --> 00:10:24,791
- [grunting]

241
00:10:24,875 --> 00:10:27,583
Uh, allow me to thank you
from the bottom of my heart.

242
00:10:27,666 --> 00:10:28,708
You helped me out without
ever once giving it

243
00:10:28,791 --> 00:10:30,208
a second thought.

244
00:10:30,291 --> 00:10:33,250
I, Subaru Natsuki,
deeply admired your selfless act

245
00:10:33,333 --> 00:10:35,541
of bravery and kindness.
- Hey, come on now.

246
00:10:35,625 --> 00:10:37,541
There's no need
for such formality.

247
00:10:37,625 --> 00:10:39,250
Once it was two
of us against three,

248
00:10:39,333 --> 00:10:41,916
those thugs lost their advantage
on the situation.

249
00:10:42,000 --> 00:10:44,166
Things might have been different
if I were alone.

250
00:10:44,250 --> 00:10:46,666
<i>- Wow, his nice guy index</i>
<i>is off the charts.</i>

251
00:10:46,750 --> 00:10:48,000
- [chuckles]

252
00:10:48,083 --> 00:10:49,750
- [grunts]

253
00:10:49,833 --> 00:10:54,083
So your Master
Swordsman Reinhard, right?

254
00:10:54,166 --> 00:10:55,583
- It's Reinhard, Subaru.

255
00:10:55,666 --> 00:10:57,125
Just Reinhard.

256
00:10:57,208 --> 00:10:59,583
<i>- We went from zero</i>
<i>to buddy-buddy fast.</i>

257
00:10:59,666 --> 00:11:02,333
Well, thanks again Reinhard.
I appreciate it.

258
00:11:02,416 --> 00:11:04,791
I shouted for help over
and over but you're the only one

259
00:11:04,875 --> 00:11:06,208
who answered my call.

260
00:11:06,291 --> 00:11:08,375
I'm so pathetic.
- Hmm.

261
00:11:08,458 --> 00:11:09,833
Don't be so down on yourself.

262
00:11:09,916 --> 00:11:11,000
For most it's too risky

263
00:11:11,083 --> 00:11:13,125
to face off
against people like them.

264
00:11:13,208 --> 00:11:15,083
Listen, as far as I'm concerned,

265
00:11:15,166 --> 00:11:16,708
you were right
to call for the guards.

266
00:11:16,791 --> 00:11:18,083
- [grunts]

267
00:11:18,166 --> 00:11:20,916
So would that make you a guard,
then?

268
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:22,583
You don't look like one.

269
00:11:22,666 --> 00:11:24,666
- Well, today I happened
to be off duty,

270
00:11:24,750 --> 00:11:26,250
so I'm not in
the standard uniform

271
00:11:26,333 --> 00:11:27,458
and I know I don't look

272
00:11:27,541 --> 00:11:29,916
particularly
intimidating either way.

273
00:11:30,000 --> 00:11:32,916
- But they did call you
master swordsman, didn't they?

274
00:11:33,000 --> 00:11:33,958
So--

275
00:11:34,041 --> 00:11:36,083
- My family is a bit unique.

276
00:11:36,166 --> 00:11:37,958
Most of the time
I don't feel like

277
00:11:38,041 --> 00:11:40,000
I live up to their expectations.

278
00:11:40,958 --> 00:11:42,333
Anyway, Subaru.
- Hmm?

279
00:11:42,416 --> 00:11:43,750
- Your name,
your clothes,

280
00:11:43,833 --> 00:11:46,083
and that haircut are unusual.

281
00:11:46,166 --> 00:11:48,000
What nation are you from?

282
00:11:48,083 --> 00:11:52,000
at the moment Lugunica is a bit
more on edge than in peacetime.

283
00:11:52,083 --> 00:11:53,625
If you're having
problems while you're here,

284
00:11:53,708 --> 00:11:55,583
I'm happy to
help out in any way I can

285
00:11:55,666 --> 00:11:56,791
- [grunts]
Would you come

286
00:11:56,875 --> 00:11:59,125
to the loot house with me?
- What?

287
00:12:00,083 --> 00:12:03,625
- Uh, never mind.
forget about it.

288
00:12:03,708 --> 00:12:06,791
I don't want to bother you,
especially on your day off.

289
00:12:06,875 --> 00:12:09,041
I'll handle the rest
of this on my own somehow.

290
00:12:09,125 --> 00:12:10,375
[chuckles]

291
00:12:10,958 --> 00:12:13,791
But I'd appreciate it
if you could deliver

292
00:12:13,875 --> 00:12:14,958
a message for me.

293
00:12:15,041 --> 00:12:16,208
- Of course,
I'd be glad to.

294
00:12:16,291 --> 00:12:19,125
What would you like me
to say and to whom?

295
00:12:19,208 --> 00:12:21,291
- Well,
I don't exactly know her name,

296
00:12:21,375 --> 00:12:24,125
but have you seen
a girl with white robes

297
00:12:24,208 --> 00:12:25,916
and silver hair
around here lately?

298
00:12:26,666 --> 00:12:29,291
- White robes
and silver hair, huh?

299
00:12:29,375 --> 00:12:32,041
- Oh, he's also
exceptionally beautiful.

300
00:12:33,291 --> 00:12:35,250
- No, it doesn't ring a bell.

301
00:12:35,333 --> 00:12:37,125
- Well, if you do happen
to see her,

302
00:12:37,208 --> 00:12:38,500
tell her not to come near

303
00:12:38,583 --> 00:12:40,583
the loot house no matter what.

304
00:12:41,166 --> 00:12:42,375
I'll find what she's been
looking for

305
00:12:42,458 --> 00:12:43,625
and bring it to her myself.

306
00:12:43,708 --> 00:12:45,166
No problem at all.
Okay?

307
00:12:45,250 --> 00:12:46,833
- Very well, then.

308
00:12:46,916 --> 00:12:49,666
If I see her then I'll be sure
to relay your message.

309
00:12:49,750 --> 00:12:51,208
- Thanks a lot.

310
00:12:52,583 --> 00:12:54,708
I'll repay you one day.
[grunts]

311
00:12:55,000 --> 00:12:57,833
- Sure.
Take care.

312
00:12:59,791 --> 00:13:01,666
[birds cawing]

313
00:13:01,750 --> 00:13:03,666
- You're looking for Felts den,
huh?

314
00:13:03,750 --> 00:13:04,833
You're close.

315
00:13:04,916 --> 00:13:05,875
Just head straight this way

316
00:13:05,958 --> 00:13:08,291
another two blocks or so.
- Great.

317
00:13:08,375 --> 00:13:10,041
Thanks.
I appreciate it, man.

318
00:13:10,125 --> 00:13:11,875
- Hey, not a problem at all,
kid.

319
00:13:11,958 --> 00:13:13,958
Now live strong
and take care.

320
00:13:14,458 --> 00:13:16,250
- The question is whether Felt
will come back there

321
00:13:16,333 --> 00:13:17,375
before the meeting.

322
00:13:17,458 --> 00:13:18,875
I'd rather catch up
with her before

323
00:13:18,958 --> 00:13:20,166
she makes her way
to the loot house

324
00:13:20,250 --> 00:13:22,208
and trade her the cell phone
for the insignia,

325
00:13:22,291 --> 00:13:24,208
which should prevent--
[grunts]

326
00:13:24,291 --> 00:13:26,041
- Oh, dear.
I'm sorry.

327
00:13:26,125 --> 00:13:27,916
Are you all right?
- Yeah, I'm fine.

328
00:13:28,000 --> 00:13:29,208
Sorry.
I don't look it,

329
00:13:29,291 --> 00:13:31,041
but toughness
is one thing I've got.

330
00:13:31,125 --> 00:13:33,708
<i>[unsettling music]</i>

331
00:13:33,791 --> 00:13:35,500
[gasping]

332
00:13:35,583 --> 00:13:40,375
[heart pounding]

333
00:13:40,458 --> 00:13:42,208
- [giggles]
What's wrong?

334
00:13:42,291 --> 00:13:44,208
You don't have to be so scared.

335
00:13:44,291 --> 00:13:46,291
I'm not going
to do anything to you.

336
00:13:46,375 --> 00:13:47,541
- What?
I'm not scared.

337
00:13:47,625 --> 00:13:49,250
Just a little surprised.
That's all.

338
00:13:49,333 --> 00:13:52,291
Whatever gave you that idea?
- Your scent.

339
00:13:52,583 --> 00:13:54,041
When people are scared,

340
00:13:54,125 --> 00:13:57,791
I can smell the fear on them
like a kind of perfume

341
00:13:57,875 --> 00:14:00,166
and you're definitely scared
right now.

342
00:14:00,250 --> 00:14:02,583
You're angry as well,
aren't you?

343
00:14:02,666 --> 00:14:03,583
At me.

344
00:14:03,666 --> 00:14:05,916
- [shudders]

345
00:14:06,000 --> 00:14:07,916
- [giggles]

346
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:09,916
[slurps]

347
00:14:10,000 --> 00:14:12,833
- [shuddering]

348
00:14:12,916 --> 00:14:14,333
- It's fine.
- [grunts]

349
00:14:14,416 --> 00:14:17,041
- I am rather curious
but now isn't the time

350
00:14:17,125 --> 00:14:18,666
to start a commotion.

351
00:14:18,750 --> 00:14:20,541
- That's not
a very nice thing to say.

352
00:14:20,625 --> 00:14:22,250
If you're too scary
that beauty of yours

353
00:14:22,333 --> 00:14:25,083
will just go to waste.
- Oh, very good.

354
00:14:25,166 --> 00:14:27,916
Conceal your hostility
and you'll be even better.

355
00:14:28,000 --> 00:14:29,500
- [stammers]

356
00:14:30,375 --> 00:14:32,708
- Well, I'll be going now.

357
00:14:32,791 --> 00:14:34,916
Something tells me
we'll meet again.

358
00:14:41,166 --> 00:14:43,041
- [inhales and exhales sharply]

359
00:14:45,208 --> 00:14:48,375
[birds cawing]

360
00:14:51,500 --> 00:14:54,291
- What a dump.
Someone actually lives here?

361
00:14:54,750 --> 00:14:56,041
[grunts]

362
00:14:57,083 --> 00:14:58,375
If I didn't know any better,

363
00:14:58,458 --> 00:15:01,458
I'd say Elsa had already
been here and trash the place.

364
00:15:01,833 --> 00:15:04,958
It's fine, I'm sure.
I don't smell blood.

365
00:15:05,041 --> 00:15:07,458
It does smell like
a bunch of garbage though.

366
00:15:07,541 --> 00:15:08,791
[grunts]

367
00:15:08,875 --> 00:15:11,041
- Hey, what do
you think you're doing peeking

368
00:15:11,125 --> 00:15:13,791
into someone's house?
You're wasting your time.

369
00:15:13,875 --> 00:15:16,125
There's nothing
worth stealing in there anyway.

370
00:15:16,208 --> 00:15:17,291
Now beat it.

371
00:15:17,375 --> 00:15:18,541
- No, hang on a second.

372
00:15:18,625 --> 00:15:19,666
That's not what I was doing.

373
00:15:19,750 --> 00:15:21,000
- Don't give me that!
- Whoa!

374
00:15:21,083 --> 00:15:22,458
Stop it!
Calm down!

375
00:15:22,541 --> 00:15:24,666
This is no time to fight!
It's gonna be dark soon!

376
00:15:24,750 --> 00:15:26,500
[gasps]
- [grunts]

377
00:15:26,583 --> 00:15:28,666
Before then,
you'd better be gone.

378
00:15:28,750 --> 00:15:31,166
- I already told you.
You've got it all wrong.

379
00:15:31,250 --> 00:15:34,250
[both grunting]

380
00:15:42,125 --> 00:15:43,875
- You don't give up, do you?

381
00:15:43,958 --> 00:15:46,666
I told you to get out of here,
so do it!

382
00:15:46,750 --> 00:15:48,500
- Stop it!
Just listen to me!

383
00:15:48,583 --> 00:15:52,916
[both grunting]

384
00:15:53,000 --> 00:15:54,958
[shouts]
- [grunts]

385
00:15:55,041 --> 00:16:01,208
- [shouting]

386
00:16:01,291 --> 00:16:02,750
[gasping]

387
00:16:02,833 --> 00:16:04,333
- [grunts]
- [whimpers]

388
00:16:04,958 --> 00:16:07,250
P--please listen to me.
Just hear me out, Felt.

389
00:16:07,333 --> 00:16:08,375
- Hmm?

390
00:16:08,458 --> 00:16:10,583
- I'm here on
important business, okay?

391
00:16:10,666 --> 00:16:12,666
How do you know my name, anyway?

392
00:16:12,750 --> 00:16:15,125
Do you want me
to steal something for you?

393
00:16:15,208 --> 00:16:16,708
You should have just said so.

394
00:16:16,791 --> 00:16:18,875
- You're the one who attacked me
right off the bat.

395
00:16:18,958 --> 00:16:19,875
This is a greedy business
you're running.

396
00:16:19,958 --> 00:16:20,875
You know that?

397
00:16:20,958 --> 00:16:21,875
Do you pride yourself

398
00:16:21,958 --> 00:16:23,291
on your sticky fingers?

399
00:16:23,375 --> 00:16:24,875
- I'm just trying
to stay alive out here.

400
00:16:24,958 --> 00:16:26,125
If it weren't for this,

401
00:16:26,208 --> 00:16:28,083
I'd be forced to sell my body.

402
00:16:28,166 --> 00:16:30,375
So what do you want with me?
Spit it out.

403
00:16:30,458 --> 00:16:31,375
- [grunts]

404
00:16:31,458 --> 00:16:32,916
There's only one thing I want

405
00:16:33,000 --> 00:16:34,625
and that's the by
the insignia you stole

406
00:16:34,708 --> 00:16:36,083
right here and now.

407
00:16:36,166 --> 00:16:38,708
- My client didn't mention
any partners when I was hired.

408
00:16:38,791 --> 00:16:39,958
Hang on.

409
00:16:40,041 --> 00:16:41,541
Are you a business rival
or something?

410
00:16:41,625 --> 00:16:43,916
Call her a rival or call her
the one who killed my parents

411
00:16:44,000 --> 00:16:45,375
or the one who killed me,
even.

412
00:16:45,458 --> 00:16:47,291
at the end of the day,
it doesn't make any difference.

413
00:16:47,375 --> 00:16:49,416
You're not making any sense,

414
00:16:49,500 --> 00:16:51,000
but when it comes down to it,

415
00:16:51,083 --> 00:16:53,750
I only care about selling
to whoever pays the most.

416
00:16:53,833 --> 00:16:56,125
If you've got an offer that
might be profitable to me,

417
00:16:56,208 --> 00:16:57,375
I'll listen.
- How shrewd.

418
00:16:57,458 --> 00:16:59,416
It's all about the money.

419
00:16:59,500 --> 00:17:01,416
I have a rare item
in my possession

420
00:17:01,500 --> 00:17:03,416
that's worth more
than 20 holy coins.

421
00:17:03,500 --> 00:17:05,333
I want to buy
your insignia with it.

422
00:17:06,000 --> 00:17:08,416
And it's something
that's in high demand nowadays.

423
00:17:08,500 --> 00:17:09,583
See?
A metia.

424
00:17:09,666 --> 00:17:10,958
- [grunts]
[camera shutter clicks]

425
00:17:11,041 --> 00:17:12,250
Huh?

426
00:17:12,333 --> 00:17:14,500
- That is the power of a metia.

427
00:17:14,583 --> 00:17:16,458
This little number
is a one-of-a-kind item

428
00:17:16,541 --> 00:17:18,916
that can capture
and freeze a moment in time.

429
00:17:19,000 --> 00:17:21,250
So, how about it?

430
00:17:21,500 --> 00:17:23,375
- Well, you don't seem
to be lying,

431
00:17:23,458 --> 00:17:26,750
but is that supposed to be me?
I look much prettier than that.

432
00:17:26,833 --> 00:17:28,416
If you look this
good without makeup,

433
00:17:28,500 --> 00:17:30,958
you're doing just fine
don't complain about

434
00:17:31,041 --> 00:17:32,458
- It is unusual.

435
00:17:32,541 --> 00:17:34,125
I'll give you that much.
- Hmm?

436
00:17:34,208 --> 00:17:36,833
But I really doubt it's worth
more than 20 holy coins.

437
00:17:36,916 --> 00:17:39,291
You're a prospective buyer
in the situation.

438
00:17:39,375 --> 00:17:41,208
You don't think I'm just gonna
believe whatever you tell me

439
00:17:41,291 --> 00:17:43,375
as fact, now do you?
Come on.

440
00:17:43,458 --> 00:17:44,458
- I see your point.

441
00:17:44,541 --> 00:17:45,958
No, probably not.

442
00:17:46,041 --> 00:17:48,625
- There's a loot house down
at the far edge of these slums.

443
00:17:48,708 --> 00:17:50,375
I think the fair thing
to do is have it appraised

444
00:17:50,458 --> 00:17:51,833
by the guy
who lives there--

445
00:17:51,916 --> 00:17:54,500
Old Man Rom.
- [grunts]

446
00:17:54,583 --> 00:17:56,958
So it still comes to that.
- Hmm?

447
00:17:57,041 --> 00:17:59,083
- Okay. Got it.
Let's go right now.

448
00:17:59,166 --> 00:18:01,000
Let's get moving on the double.
- [stammers]

449
00:18:02,041 --> 00:18:03,375
- We'll just have him
take a look at it

450
00:18:03,458 --> 00:18:05,208
and then get out of there
as soon as possible.

451
00:18:05,291 --> 00:18:06,541
- Take it easy!

452
00:18:11,708 --> 00:18:14,208
What's your problem?
slow down.

453
00:18:14,291 --> 00:18:15,250
Why are you in such a hurry?

454
00:18:15,333 --> 00:18:17,083
- [groans]

455
00:18:18,375 --> 00:18:21,250
- You're sweating like crazy.

456
00:18:21,333 --> 00:18:23,416
Oh, well.
Anyway, live strong.

457
00:18:23,500 --> 00:18:24,500
- Someone else here
in the slums

458
00:18:24,583 --> 00:18:25,583
said that a little earlier.

459
00:18:25,666 --> 00:18:27,625
Is it like
a slogan or something?

460
00:18:27,708 --> 00:18:29,541
- Look, don't let me
in with those other guys.

461
00:18:29,625 --> 00:18:32,208
They're all talk.
They don't live strong at all.

462
00:18:32,291 --> 00:18:34,333
They're nothing,
but a bunch of Stingy losers

463
00:18:34,416 --> 00:18:36,166
who've got nothing going
for them.

464
00:18:36,250 --> 00:18:38,750
- Wow, that's kind of harsh.
Judgmental much?

465
00:18:39,541 --> 00:18:41,250
- [panting]

466
00:18:42,875 --> 00:18:45,458
I'm not like the other
people around here, okay?

467
00:18:45,541 --> 00:18:47,250
I have no intention
of living out the rest

468
00:18:47,333 --> 00:18:50,625
of my life in these
dingy dirty back alleys.

469
00:18:51,208 --> 00:18:52,208
- Is that so?

470
00:18:52,291 --> 00:18:53,583
And you think 20 holy coins

471
00:18:53,666 --> 00:18:55,708
will make these dreams
of yours come true?

472
00:18:55,791 --> 00:18:57,000
- Not by themselves,

473
00:18:57,083 --> 00:18:59,208
but it would be a huge leap
toward my goal.

474
00:18:59,291 --> 00:19:01,208
Even if I were alone,
it's not as if I couldn't

475
00:19:01,291 --> 00:19:03,083
get by with some effort.

476
00:19:03,500 --> 00:19:06,250
- If you were alone?
- Just forget it.

477
00:19:06,333 --> 00:19:09,541
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

478
00:19:09,625 --> 00:19:11,958
- Oh.

479
00:19:12,041 --> 00:19:13,958
[chuckles]

480
00:19:14,041 --> 00:19:16,208
What are you standing there
smirking about?

481
00:19:16,291 --> 00:19:18,166
You really piss me off.
You know that?

482
00:19:18,250 --> 00:19:20,208
- Don't worry about it.
- [grunts]

483
00:19:20,291 --> 00:19:21,375
H--hey!

484
00:19:21,458 --> 00:19:23,958
What are you doing?
Stop!

485
00:19:24,041 --> 00:19:26,250
- I'll make this
all work out somehow.

486
00:19:26,333 --> 00:19:27,791
It's something only I can do.

487
00:19:27,875 --> 00:19:29,416
- Don't get all sentimental
on me

488
00:19:29,500 --> 00:19:31,083
while you're babbling nonsense!

489
00:19:31,166 --> 00:19:32,416
I'll bite you!

490
00:19:32,500 --> 00:19:33,958
<i>- It's not just for her.</i>

491
00:19:34,041 --> 00:19:36,583
<i>I'll change the fate</i>
<i>that's waiting for me.</i>

492
00:19:37,500 --> 00:19:38,791
<i>And to do that, I'll...</i>

493
00:19:38,875 --> 00:19:41,083
- I told you
to cut it out!

494
00:19:41,166 --> 00:19:45,875
[chomps]
- [screams]

495
00:19:49,041 --> 00:19:50,791
- Hmm.

496
00:19:50,875 --> 00:19:52,916
So this is a metia.

497
00:19:53,000 --> 00:19:54,875
Well, I've heard
of them but I've never seen one

498
00:19:54,958 --> 00:19:57,458
with my own eyes.
- It's a fairly delicate device.

499
00:19:57,541 --> 00:19:59,083
So I suggest
you handle it with care.

500
00:19:59,166 --> 00:20:00,666
Just think
of it along the lines of

501
00:20:00,750 --> 00:20:02,666
if you break it,
you have to die.

502
00:20:03,166 --> 00:20:05,125
In the sense
that you get no do-overs.

503
00:20:05,208 --> 00:20:08,166
- Yeah.
I'm definitely impressed.

504
00:20:08,250 --> 00:20:11,500
If I were to sell this
I'd take no less than 15.

505
00:20:11,583 --> 00:20:13,583
No, 20 holy coins,
'cause I'd likely

506
00:20:13,666 --> 00:20:15,416
not come across one again.
