00:41:00,708 --> 00:41:02,375
- If I had the ability
to do that,

1011
00:41:02,458 --> 00:41:03,875
I'd certainly be proud.

1012
00:41:03,958 --> 00:41:05,333
This friend of yours,

1013
00:41:05,416 --> 00:41:07,750
I found her running around
the streets quite frightened

1014
00:41:07,833 --> 00:41:09,916
and desperate
and she asked for my help,

1015
00:41:10,000 --> 00:41:11,625
so I came here.

1016
00:41:11,958 --> 00:41:14,708
- It's her.
- Now, hang on a second.

1017
00:41:14,791 --> 00:41:16,166
If she hadn't brought Reinhard
here,

1018
00:41:16,250 --> 00:41:19,000
who knows if we'd even
be having this conversation?

1019
00:41:19,083 --> 00:41:20,875
Just take a look at this face
and spare me

1020
00:41:20,958 --> 00:41:22,875
the ice statue punishment, okay?

1021
00:41:22,958 --> 00:41:24,708
- I wouldn't do anything
that violent.

1022
00:41:24,791 --> 00:41:26,875
And was your face have
to do with any--

1023
00:41:26,958 --> 00:41:28,375
[both grunting]
- Subaru!

1024
00:41:36,208 --> 00:41:38,208
- She'll go for the gut.
[grunts]

1025
00:41:38,291 --> 00:41:40,458
Get away!

1026
00:41:40,958 --> 00:41:43,666
- [grunts]
That boy got in my way again.

1027
00:41:43,750 --> 00:41:45,458
- That's enough, Elsa.

1028
00:41:48,166 --> 00:41:49,458
- Before long,

1029
00:41:49,541 --> 00:41:52,833
I will disembowel every last one
of you here in this room.

1030
00:41:54,625 --> 00:41:56,041
Until that moment comes,

1031
00:41:56,125 --> 00:41:58,125
be sure to take care
of yourselves.

1032
00:42:00,958 --> 00:42:02,583
- Are you all right?

1033
00:42:02,666 --> 00:42:05,208
- My being all right isn't
what's most important right now,

1034
00:42:05,291 --> 00:42:07,291
but are you all right?

1035
00:42:07,375 --> 00:42:09,916
That was far too reckless.

1036
00:42:10,000 --> 00:42:11,875
- [grunts]
Oh, it was no problem.

1037
00:42:13,333 --> 00:42:15,958
Now, it sure took
a long time to get here,

1038
00:42:16,041 --> 00:42:18,291
but the good news
is I finally made it.

1039
00:42:19,458 --> 00:42:22,750
My name is Subaru Natsuki
and I just risked it all

1040
00:42:22,833 --> 00:42:24,208
to save your life
from a dangerous

1041
00:42:24,291 --> 00:42:26,833
and heinous villain.
Is that okay?

1042
00:42:28,208 --> 00:42:31,166
- Okay?
- It means are we clear on that?

1043
00:42:31,250 --> 00:42:33,041
So, okay?

1044
00:42:33,125 --> 00:42:35,208
- Uh, okay.

1045
00:42:35,291 --> 00:42:37,291
- I, your rescuer,
am the one who saved your life,

1046
00:42:37,375 --> 00:42:40,125
and you are the heroine I saved
from the clutches of evil,

1047
00:42:40,208 --> 00:42:41,791
so wouldn't that mean you should
repay me in kind?

1048
00:42:41,875 --> 00:42:42,916
Wouldn't it, huh?

1049
00:42:43,000 --> 00:42:44,916
- Yes, I understand,

1050
00:42:45,000 --> 00:42:47,791
but only if whatever you want
reward wise is within my power,

1051
00:42:47,875 --> 00:42:49,958
of course.
- That sounds fair to me.

1052
00:42:50,041 --> 00:42:52,250
In that case,
I have only one request,

1053
00:42:52,333 --> 00:42:55,625
and that request is...

1054
00:42:55,708 --> 00:42:56,750
- [gasps]

1055
00:42:56,833 --> 00:42:58,166
- [chuckles]

1056
00:43:01,083 --> 00:43:02,833
I want you to tell
me what your name is.

1057
00:43:06,250 --> 00:43:07,916
- [giggles]

1058
00:43:08,250 --> 00:43:09,916
Amelia,
- Huh?

1059
00:43:10,000 --> 00:43:11,833
- [giggles]

1060
00:43:11,916 --> 00:43:15,791
Your price was easy to pay.
My name is Amelia.

1061
00:43:16,666 --> 00:43:18,166
Only Amelia.

1062
00:43:19,291 --> 00:43:21,333
Thanks for saving me, Subaru.

1063
00:43:23,000 --> 00:43:24,833
- [gasping]

1064
00:43:26,916 --> 00:43:30,000
<i>All those times, I got hurt,</i>
<i>all the crying I did,</i>

1065
00:43:30,083 --> 00:43:31,333
<i>all the pain I felt,</i>

1066
00:43:31,416 --> 00:43:34,625
<i>all the fighting</i>
<i>with my life on the line,</i>

1067
00:43:34,708 --> 00:43:37,375
<i>and my reward was her name</i>
<i>and a single smile.</i>

1068
00:43:38,583 --> 00:43:40,166
[exhales]

1069
00:43:40,250 --> 00:43:44,166
Oh man.
Talk about unequal compensation.

1070
00:43:47,583 --> 00:43:48,708
- Anyway, Subaru,

1071
00:43:48,791 --> 00:43:50,541
I'm impressed you're still
able to stand.

1072
00:43:50,625 --> 00:43:52,041
- I was lucky this thing
was there

1073
00:43:52,125 --> 00:43:53,458
to grab her protection.

1074
00:43:53,541 --> 00:43:55,875
Otherwise,
I'd be in two pieces right now.

1075
00:43:55,958 --> 00:43:59,041
- True.
If not for this--

1076
00:43:59,125 --> 00:44:00,041
What the...
- [gasps]

1077
00:44:00,125 --> 00:44:01,708
- [stammering]

1078
00:44:04,291 --> 00:44:08,083
Uh-oh, I should
have seen this coming.

1079
00:44:08,791 --> 00:44:10,750
- [gasps]
Subaru!

1080
00:44:10,833 --> 00:44:11,958
Subaru!

1081
00:44:14,666 --> 00:44:16,458
<i>- Man.</i>

1082
00:44:16,541 --> 00:44:19,958
<i>She's so cute when</i>
<i>she's panicking like that.</i>

1083
00:44:20,208 --> 00:44:22,541
<i>A fantasy in another world.</i>

1084
00:44:25,250 --> 00:44:27,416
- There.
His treatment is complete.

1085
00:44:27,500 --> 00:44:29,583
He should be over the hump now.

1086
00:44:29,666 --> 00:44:30,875
By the way, Miss Amelia,

1087
00:44:30,958 --> 00:44:34,875
what's the nature
of your relation to Subaru?

1088
00:44:34,958 --> 00:44:37,416
- An acquaintance?
- Hmm?

1089
00:44:37,500 --> 00:44:40,500
- Honestly, I don't recall
ever seeing him before.

1090
00:44:40,583 --> 00:44:41,875
When we met earlier today,

1091
00:44:41,958 --> 00:44:44,000
I believe it was
the very first time.

1092
00:44:44,083 --> 00:44:45,500
- But he was looking
for you,

1093
00:44:45,583 --> 00:44:47,291
said he had something
to give you.

1094
00:44:47,375 --> 00:44:48,916
Odd behavior from a stranger.

1095
00:44:49,000 --> 00:44:51,625
- Yes.
It is rather peculiar.

1096
00:44:51,708 --> 00:44:53,291
- So what do you propose we do
with him, then?

1097
00:44:53,375 --> 00:44:54,708
I'd be glad to take him

1098
00:44:54,791 --> 00:44:57,208
to my home as a guest,
at least while he's healing.

1099
00:44:57,291 --> 00:44:59,791
- [grunts]
I'll take him home with me.

1100
00:44:59,875 --> 00:45:02,916
That way I can find out
what's really going on.

1101
00:45:03,000 --> 00:45:04,875
More importantly,

1102
00:45:04,958 --> 00:45:07,291
what will become
of that girl and the old man?

1103
00:45:08,333 --> 00:45:09,416
- In an official capacity,

1104
00:45:09,500 --> 00:45:11,750
I cannot overlook
what they've done here.

1105
00:45:11,833 --> 00:45:14,416
However, as luck would have it,

1106
00:45:14,500 --> 00:45:16,500
I just so happened
to be off duty today.

1107
00:45:16,583 --> 00:45:17,916
- [giggles]

1108
00:45:18,333 --> 00:45:19,833
Well, aren't you a bad knight?

1109
00:45:20,625 --> 00:45:22,458
- [whimpers]

1110
00:45:23,083 --> 00:45:26,125
- So this old man is part
of your family, I take it?

1111
00:45:26,708 --> 00:45:28,458
- Yeah, something like that,
I guess.

1112
00:45:28,541 --> 00:45:31,125
Old Man Rom's the only person
I have in this world.

1113
00:45:31,208 --> 00:45:32,791
[grunts]

1114
00:45:32,875 --> 00:45:35,125
I suppose he's like my grandpa.

1115
00:45:35,208 --> 00:45:36,833
- I see.

1116
00:45:36,916 --> 00:45:39,125
I only have one
family member, too.

1117
00:45:39,208 --> 00:45:41,916
He's always asleep at the most
important moments, though.

1118
00:45:42,000 --> 00:45:44,166
'Course, I wouldn't say that
out loud when he's awake.

1119
00:45:44,250 --> 00:45:46,125
I'd never hear the end of it.

1120
00:45:46,208 --> 00:45:47,375
- Considering what I did,

1121
00:45:47,458 --> 00:45:49,500
I figured you'd be
a lot harder on me.

1122
00:45:50,958 --> 00:45:53,958
You saved my life back there
and I can't let a debt go unpaid

1123
00:45:54,041 --> 00:45:56,291
so I'll return
what I stole from you, okay?

1124
00:45:56,958 --> 00:45:59,333
If it's important,
I suggest you keep it hidden

1125
00:45:59,416 --> 00:46:00,916
so no one can steal it again.

1126
00:46:01,000 --> 00:46:02,875
- I appreciate the advice,
though it's a little strange

1127
00:46:02,958 --> 00:46:04,708
to hear it from you.
- [gasps]

1128
00:46:06,000 --> 00:46:08,625
[gasps]
- [grunting]

1129
00:46:08,708 --> 00:46:11,083
- What are you doing?
- Hey, you're hurting me.

1130
00:46:11,166 --> 00:46:12,750
Let go of my arm.

1131
00:46:13,000 --> 00:46:15,458
- [gasps]
This can't be possible.

1132
00:46:15,541 --> 00:46:17,208
What's your name?
- Huh?

1133
00:46:17,291 --> 00:46:18,541
It's Felt.
Why do--

1134
00:46:18,625 --> 00:46:21,083
- Family name,
and just how old are you?

1135
00:46:21,166 --> 00:46:24,500
- Look I don't have anything
fancy like a family name.

1136
00:46:24,583 --> 00:46:27,333
I'm about 15,
if I had to guess.

1137
00:46:27,416 --> 00:46:28,916
I don't know my birthday.

1138
00:46:29,000 --> 00:46:31,291
Just let me go.
- Sorry, Miss Amelia,

1139
00:46:31,375 --> 00:46:34,583
but I'm afraid that I can't keep
my promise to you at this time.

1140
00:46:34,916 --> 00:46:37,291
I'll be taking this girl
with me for further questioning.

1141
00:46:37,583 --> 00:46:39,125
- May I ask you why?

1142
00:46:39,208 --> 00:46:41,500
If it's just for stealing
my insignia, then--

1143
00:46:41,583 --> 00:46:44,875
- That's left alone
is no small crime, certainly,

1144
00:46:44,958 --> 00:46:46,625
but if I overlook what's
unfolding before me

1145
00:46:46,708 --> 00:46:47,750
at this moment,

1146
00:46:47,833 --> 00:46:49,041
I know it would be
the greatest crime

1147
00:46:49,125 --> 00:46:50,375
of them all.

1148
00:46:50,458 --> 00:46:51,958
I'll need you
to come along with me.

1149
00:46:52,041 --> 00:46:53,583
I'm sorry,
but I simply can't allow you

1150
00:46:53,666 --> 00:46:55,625
to refuse.
- Get over yourself.

1151
00:46:55,708 --> 00:46:58,291
Just because
you saved me doesn't mean you--

1152
00:46:59,250 --> 00:47:02,041
- That little move didn't seem
very knightly, either.

1153
00:47:02,125 --> 00:47:03,958
- I was careful not
to use too much.

1154
00:47:04,041 --> 00:47:05,041
Miss Amelia,

1155
00:47:05,125 --> 00:47:06,375
I will most likely be calling

1156
00:47:06,458 --> 00:47:08,125
upon you again very soon.

1157
00:47:08,958 --> 00:47:10,750
I hope you understand.

1158
00:47:13,541 --> 00:47:16,750
Please take good care of Subaru.
He's been through a lot.

1159
00:47:18,250 --> 00:47:19,416
[both grunting]

1160
00:47:21,708 --> 00:47:24,833
Tonight may be our last chance

1161
00:47:24,916 --> 00:47:27,375
to gaze calmly at the Moon.

1162
00:47:37,625 --> 00:47:42,000
<i>- ♪ Oh please don't let me die</i>
<i>Waiting for your touch ♪</i>

1163
